_json.gridTitle: 24 Tips on How to Paint Kitchen Cabinets
_json.description: Consider Filling Open Grain - Some types of wood have grain with many open pores. Oak is a good example. The pores show through finishes and are especially noticeable under paint. It’s OK to leave the grain showing, but if you want a smooth, grain-free look, you’ll have to fill the pores before painting. There are a few methods.
